To find the matrix that corresponds to projecting onto a vector, we use the formula for the projection matrix. For a vector $\mathbf{v} = \begin{pmatrix} a \\ b \end{pmatrix}$, the projection matrix $\mathbf{P}$ is given by: \[
\mathbf{P} = \frac{\mathbf{v} \mathbf{v}^T}{\mathbf{v}^T \mathbf{v}}
\]
For $\mathbf{v} = \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 7 \end{pmatrix}$, this becomes: \[
\mathbf{P} = \frac{1}{1^2 + 7^2} \begin{pmatrix} 1 & 7 \end{pmatrix} \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 7 \end{pmatrix} = \frac{1}{50} \begin{pmatrix} 1 & 7 \\ 7 & 49 \end{pmatrix}
\]
Thus, the projection matrix is: \[
\begin{pmatrix} \frac{1}{50} & \frac{7}{50} \\ \frac{7}{50} & \frac{49}{50} \end{pmatrix}
\]
